	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I skimmed through these pages just because I'm bored, and couldn't help but chuckle at the bull**** that gets posted here.  So anybody wanting to know more about these gauntlets, misinformed dumbasses, and n00bs who will would like some info on their armor, listen up!<BR>
<BR>
Cobalt Gauntlets are an incredibly rare drop off the Drolvarg Captain from Karnor's Castle.  He hits for about 145 max, and has a good deal of hit points (at least 5k).  He spawns all over the tower, which is the area you are at when you first cross the moat.  He's a fairly common spawn, and will usually spawn 1 or 2 times each hour.<BR>
<BR>
You usually need to be 50+ as a tank to get a group here.  You'll need a full group.  Couple of tanks, shammy, cleric, and enchanter are perfect.  Tower is a fairly easy camp if everybody knows what they are doing.  <BR>
<BR>
Captain's common drop is Drolvarg Mantle, and it's about all he drops most of the time.  Expect to be here for a few days if you want anything good at all.  One day he spawned 21 times and dropped 21 mantles.  The next day I camped him he spawned about 13 times and dropped 13 mantles.  The sentries you'll be killing drop good loot more often, as I got a full set of Flayed Skin, Singing Steel Boots, and lots of nice gems during my time here.  <BR>
<BR>
The good thing is that most groups are need before greed, so if cobalt drops you'll only be rolling against the other warrior, or sometimes you'll get it by default.  If at all possible, become leader of the group so you can ensure NBG.  <BR>
<BR>
Sorry for the long post, but I felt that I needed to actually post some real info here.  Half the people here are probably level 10 warriors getting excited about seeing something better than 2 copper drop.  I have been here, and I know how it works, so I know what I'm talkin about.<BR>
<BR>
I'll be goin back again tomorrow, as I have yet to get my Cobalt Gaunts, much less see them drop.<BR>
<BR>
Lochraven Iceblade<BR>
51 Champion of The Nameless<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
